.TH LEO 1 "March 2026" "1.0" "Leo Language Manual"
.SH NAME
leo \- interpreter for the leo programming language
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B leo
[\fIfile.leo\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B leo
is the command-line interface for executing scripts written in the leo language.
It processes each provided source file in the order they appear on the command line.
.PP
If no files are provided, it does nothing.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I file.leo
The path to a source file ending in the .leo extension. The interpreter will
load, parse, and execute the file before moving to the next argument.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success. All provided scripts were executed without unhandled exceptions.
.TP
.B 1
Failure. One or more scripts encountered a syntax error or a runtime crash.
.SH EXAMPLES
.B leo script.leo
.IP
Execute a single file.
.PP
.B leo main.leo utils.leo config.leo
.IP
Execute multiple files sequentially.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR python (1),
.BR lua (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Developed by Michał Pociecha-Łoś.
